.\" shorthand for double quote that works everywhere.
.ds q \N'34'
.TH WMT __drivermansuffix__ __vendorversion__
.SH NAME
wmt \- WonderMedia WM8505 video driver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B "Section \*qDevice\*q"
.BI "  Identifier \*q" devname \*q
.B "  Driver \*qwmt\*q"
\ \ ...
.B EndSection
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wmt
is an __xservername__ driver for the WonderMedia WM8505 display
controller and its 2D Graphics Engine (GE).  It drives the display
through the kernel's
.B wmt-drm
KMS device and accelerates solid fills and copies using the GE via
the EXA acceleration architecture.
.SH SUPPORTED HARDWARE
The
.B wmt
driver supports the WM8505 display controller (GOVRH) and 2D Graphics
Engine exposed by the in-kernel
.B wmt-drm
DRM/KMS driver.
.SH CONFIGURATION DETAILS
The driver is normally selected automatically by an OutputClass that
matches the
.B wmt-drm
kernel driver, so no manual configuration is required.
.PP
The following driver
.B Option
flags are supported:
.TP
.BI "Option \*qAccel\*q \*q" boolean \*q
Enable or disable GE acceleration.  Default: enabled.
.TP
.BI "Option \*qTearFree\*q \*q" boolean \*q
Enable double-buffered, vblank-synchronised page flipping to eliminate
tearing.  Default: enabled.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
__xservername__(__appmansuffix__), Xorg(__appmansuffix__), xorg.conf(__filemansuffix__)
